Italy Needs a 10-Year ‘Vision’ for its Economy, Tremonti Says

-- B y   G r e g o r y   V i s c u s i
-- 
2011-09-17T10:48:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-17/italy-needs-a-10-year-vision-for-its-economy-tremonti-says.html
Italy “has a platform for a
balanced budget, but on that platform we have to build a vision
that’s not just for one year but for a decade,” Finance
Minister  Giulio Tremonti  said. “That vision must be three-
dimensional, dynamic and modern,” he said after a meeting of
European Union finance ministers in Wroclaw,  Poland .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
